# Package Layer Boundaries

The monorepo has a strict one-way dependency chain. Each layer may only import from layers below it:

```
excalidraw-app           → can import from: @excalidraw/excalidraw, @excalidraw/element, @excalidraw/math, @excalidraw/common
@excalidraw/excalidraw   → can import from: @excalidraw/element, @excalidraw/math, @excalidraw/common
@excalidraw/element      → can import from: @excalidraw/math, @excalidraw/common
@excalidraw/math         → can import from: @excalidraw/common only
@excalidraw/common       → no internal imports allowed
```

## Forbidden imports

- `packages/math/` MUST NOT import from `@excalidraw/element` or `@excalidraw/excalidraw`
- `packages/common/` MUST NOT import from any other `@excalidraw/*` package
- `packages/element/` MUST NOT import from `@excalidraw/excalidraw`
- `packages/excalidraw/` MUST NOT import from `excalidraw-app/`

## How to verify

1. Run `grep -r "from.*@excalidraw/excalidraw" packages/element/` — must return no results
2. Run `grep -r "from.*@excalidraw/element\|from.*@excalidraw/excalidraw" packages/math/` — must return no results
3. Run `grep -r "from.*@excalidraw" packages/common/` — must return no results
4. Run `yarn test:typecheck` — circular or upward imports produce TypeScript resolution errors